The paper focuses on question answering (QA) systems and their sensitivity to different ways of expressing the same information need. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is often associated with sub-categories such as computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses neural networks as a scoring model, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural engineering (cs.NE).
